    [ctns_front]
Linear Function<br/>Point-Slope Form
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:80%;font-size:90%;']
For a given point $$(x_1,y_1)$$ and slope $$m$$, the Point-Slope Form is given by
$|y-y_1 = m(x - x_1).|$
    [/ctns_back]
    
    [ctns_backspeak]
For a given point x sub 1 , y sub 1 and the slope
m, the Point-Slope Form is given by the expression
y minus y sub one = m times the quantity of x minus x sub 1.
    [/ctns_backspeak]
    

[/ctns_make]
